Rayman Fiesta Run is an awesome vibrant automatic runner that will keep you on your toes at all times if you're a completionist. There's a lot of value to be had from your purchase, as the amount of levels is insane. My only real complaint would be the lack of any cloud save. There are also IAP items that you can potentially buy with in-game cash, but you'll have to grind super hard. They're 100% optional though, and not in the way AAA publishers use these words as of late, merely serving the purpose of making the game easier and less challenging.

Awesome! This game improves on everything that its predecessor, Rayman Jungle Run did good. It has much more levels, a lot more artworks, a wide variety of heroes to unlock without having to buy them. Probably my favorite thing about this game is that it has a whole new bonus world in it (the candy world) and that it has a Nightmare Mode in it which you can unlock by reaching Rank (or level) 18, where if you die, you have to start all over. It's pretty tough and challenging. And man do I adore Gourmand Land. It's pretty addictive too, and the soundtrack is by far the best I've heard in a 2D modern platformer.

You might expect this to be an endless runner, but it's actually a level based 2D platformer where your character runs automatically and you tell them when to jump and attack. It's based on the absolutely fantastic game Rayman Legends, with the same super fun physics and parkour, and this game is excellent too! If you liked Rayman: Jungle Run, you will enjoy this one too, it's practically the same game with new levels with a little more graphical detail and slightly different progression system.  In this game, you don't have to go in order, you can play any level you unlocked by collecting enough lums. Another difference is that there are no extra lives that can be picked up in the levels. They can be purchased for lums in the beginning of a level.  The most irritating thing are these micro transactions, which I didn't use, but still, it's annoying that the game shoves these items in my face that I can buy to "legally cheat". I completed every level with maximum points, but still, I couldn't buy the most expensive picture. Pictures, btw, are inside the games folder already, so the fact that they made them unlockable, is ridiculous too.
